PERTH (miningweekly.com) – Gold miner Newcrest Mining has invested a further A$325 500 in fellow listed Antipa Minerals to maintain its 9.9% shareholding in the company. Antipa earlier this year announced plans to raise A$25-million through an institutional share placement and a share purchase plan (SPP) to maintain its 35% interest in the Citadel joint venture with major Rio Tinto. Following the completion of the placement and the SPP, the company has now raised a total of A$2.53-million, and holds more than A$30-million in cash to pursue its aggressive exploration programme in 2021.